<item>
            <title>[LU-16561] allow &apos;lfs find -printf&apos; field widths</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16561</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For implementing &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find -ls&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; it would be useful to allow specifying the field width for the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;%x&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; operators, rather than forcing the use of a full tabstop with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;\t&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (which is often too large a field width and doesn&apos;t always work properly).&#160; Something like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;%12s&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to have the file size printed with 12-char fields (leading space) or &quot;&lt;tt&gt;%06U&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to have the file UID printed with leading zeroes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
